Daughter of Earth, the chaste TRUFFELIA

                           Truffelia. l. 414. (Lycoperdon Tuber) Truffle. Clandestine marriage. This fungus never appears above ground, requiring little air, and, perhaps, no light. It is found by dogs or swine, who hunt it by the smell. Other plants which have no buds or branches on their stems, as the grasses, shoot out numerous stoles or scions under ground; and this the more, as their tops or herbs are eaten by cattle, and thus preserve themselves.
